<br>
You know ::takes a sip of her wine:: when Zeus made me a goddess after I helped the Olympians defend the Titans, I thought that it would be easy. Boy was I wrong. Its just that, well...how do I put this....  When I was a Titan, I didn't have to worked for anything really, it was just a long way down easy street. But the Titans were more barbaric but besides that, things are more strict here than I thought they would be.<br>
 <br>
::takes a bit of one of the sweets. a servant comes and offers the plate of sweets to Amphitrite:: care for a sweet? Anyways, I am not saying I am unhappy here, but I need help adjusting my ways to the ways of the Olympians and the first person I thought of to help me was you. I now pledge to be more serious as far as my job goes. I'm going to Rome to watch my counterpart Victoria, for they love her there, even the armies there do. So I will watch her for awhle to see how she works when she determines the winner of the games. court cases, wars and gladiator events. <br>
<br>
Second, I am no longer on strike. People are literally flocking to my temple, lawyers, generals, and athletes from all over ::laughs:: I don't think my priests and priestesses have seen so many worshippers at once. I'm also ending the strike because of that rift with the Roman gods coming through. I don't have to worry abut Victoria because we are good friends, but the other gods do.<br>
<br>
But if anyone, even the gods, want victory, they will have to earn it as I must earn my respect from now . If a lawyer wants to win a case, he will have to think hard on what to show the jury. If a general wants to win a battle, he will have to train his troops hard and think hard of a strategic battle plan, if an athletie or gladiator wants to win, they will have to train and pactice harder than ever each day if they can. <br>
<br>
If a god wants to win something, he or she will have to work as hard as they mortals will. Well besides you ::smiles:: this is my gift to you for listening to me right now and for being a good friend to me through all of this. And if someone cheats, their victory will be completely bittersweet, and the loser will be more appeciated than the victor. ::looks to Amphitrite:: So what do you think of my new policy Amphitrite?? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamphitritegoddessofthesea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amphitrite Goddess of the Sea</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_cyanspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/24/01 2:21:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Brand New Policy</span><hr size=1> ::looks blankly, as a single tear rolls her face::<br>
